Title: Return of the Obra Dinn - Narrated Modeling Mega Timelapse
Description:
Creating characters, objects, and scenes for "Return of the Obra Dinn" from 2015-2018
*CONTAINS HOURS OF SPOILERS AND DRONING NARRATION*

This timelapse shows all my 3D-related work on Obra Dinn, from May 2015 (one year after development started), up to the game's initial release in October 2018. The timelapse 3D data was captured during development using custom tools, then re-cammed and narrated after release to produce this exhausting video.

https://youtu.be/qZFoBvJf8Ug is a tastefully stylized presentation of this same 3D timelapse data, minus the character modeling/painting and the commentary.

Title: Matt Rosenberg (@nthmonkey) on Threads
Description: My brother in law died in June. Heart attack. Four hours in the hospital and gone. And then the bills came. He’d let his insurance lapse two months prior. Bills were a few thousand here for the cardiologist, another few there for the ER docs, a bit for the radiologist. I helped my sister-in-law negotiate these down but they weren’t back breakers. Then the hospital bill came: $195k. This is a story about that.

Title: Why We Need More Programmers, Not Fewer
Description:
TL/DR The conventional wisdom is that AI will reduce the demand for programmers. I manage engineering teams and program with LLMs every day, and I am seeing something different.
Programmers who know how to work with LLMs can be 3-10x faster for specific tasks. Given that the size of our work backlog is only limited by our vision and ambition, these super-productive individuals will be more in demand, not less.
